---
import Layout from '@/components/Layout.astro';
import MediaPlaceholder from '@/components/MediaPlaceholder.astro';
---
<Layout title="Release Ball - Performance Kit" description="Myofascial release techniques using a lacrosse or massage ball">
  <div class="bg-surface py-16">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="text-center mb-12">
        <h1 class="text-4xl font-heading text-secondary mb-4">RELEASE BALL</h1>
        <p class="text-lg font-serif text-muted-foreground max-w-3xl mx-auto">
          Myofascial release techniques using a lacrosse or massage ball to relieve muscle tension and improve mobility.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-8 mb-12">
        <div>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-heading text-secondary mb-4 bg-[#8a1e1e] text-white px-3 py-2 rounded">PURPOSE</h2>
          <p class="text-muted-foreground mb-4">The release ball is used for self-myofascial release (SMR) to alleviate muscle tightness, improve blood flow, and enhance recovery. It targets trigger points and knots in the muscles.</p>
          <p class="text-muted">Equipment needed: Lacrosse ball, massage ball, or similar firm ball</p>
          <p class="text-muted">Difficulty level: Beginner</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-heading text-secondary mb-4 bg-[#8a1e1e] text-white px-3 py-2 rounded">COMMON AREAS TO TARGET</h2>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-muted-foreground">
            <li>Upper back (thoracic spine)</li>
            <li>Glutes and piriformis</li>
            <li>Quadriceps and IT band</li>
            <li>Hamstrings</li>
            <li>Calves</li>
            <li>Feet (plantar fascia)</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="mb-12">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-heading text-secondary mb-4 bg-[#8a1e1e] text-white px-3 py-2 rounded">TECHNIQUE</h2>
        <ol class="list-decimal list-inside space-y-3 text-muted-foreground">
          <li>Place the ball on the target area (e.g., under your glute while sitting or lying down).</li>
          <li>Apply gentle pressure by leaning into the ball, using your body weight.</li>
          <li>Slowly roll the ball to search for tender spots (trigger points).</li>
          <li>Once you find a tender spot, hold pressure on it for 20-30 seconds or until the pain decreases by about 50%.</li>
          <li>Move slowly to the next spot and repeat.</li>
          <li>Breathe deeply and relax into the pressure.</li>
        </ol>
      </div>

      <div class="mb-12">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-heading text-secondary mb-4 bg-[#8a1e1e] text-white px-3 py-2 rounded">EXERCISE DEMONSTRATIONS</h2>
        <div class="space-y-6">
          <div class="border border-border rounded-lg p-4 bg-background">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-heading text-secondary mb-2">GLUTE RELEASE</h3>
            <div class="relative w-full h-0 pb-[56.25%] bg-panel rounded-lg">
              <div class="absolute inset-0 flex items-center justify-center text-muted">
                <div class="text-center p-4">
                  <svg class="w-16 h-16 mx-auto mb-2 text-muted-300" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                    <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="1.5" d="M14.752 11.168l-3.197-2.132A1 1 0 0010 9.87v4.263a1 1 0 001.555.832l3.197-2.132a1 1 0 000-1.664z"></path>
                    <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="1.5" d="M21 12a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z"></path>
                  </svg>
                  <p class="text-sm">Illustration coming soon</p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <p class="mt-2 text-center text-sm text-muted">Sit on the ball, place it under one glute, and roll slowly to find tender spots.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="border border-border rounded-lg p-4 bg-background">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-heading text-secondary mb-2">FOOT RELEASE (PLANTAR FASCIA)</h3>
            <div class="relative w-full h-0 pb-[56.25%] bg-panel rounded-lg">
              <div class="absolute inset-0 flex items-center justify-center text-muted">
                <div class="text-center p-4">
                  <svg class="w-16 h-16 mx-auto mb-2 text-muted-300" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                    <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="1.5" d="M14.752 11.168l-3.197-2.132A1 1 0 0010 9.87v4.263a1 1 0 001.555.832l3.197-2.132a1 1 0 000-1.664z"></path>
                    <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="1.5" d="M21 12a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z"></path>
                  </svg>
                  <p class="text-sm">Illustration coming soon</p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <p class="mt-2 text-center text-sm text-muted">Stand or sit, place the ball under your foot, and roll from heel to toe.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="pt-6 border-t border-border">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-heading text-secondary mb-4 bg-[#8a1e1e] text-white px-3 py-2 rounded">SAFETY TIPS</h2>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-muted-foreground">
          <li>Avoid rolling directly on bones or joints.</li>
          <li>Do not roll on injured or inflamed areas without professional guidance.</li>
          <li>If you feel sharp or shooting pain, stop immediately.</li>
          <li>Stay hydrated after SMR to help flush out toxins.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
